hich one of the following is the most common causative organism of mastitis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Clostridium perfringens","Haemophilus influenzae","Pseudomonas aeruginosa","Staphylococcus aureus","Streptococcus pyogenes"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStaphylococcus aureus\u003C/strong\u003E is the most common cause of mastitis, accounting for approximately 80% of cases. The organism typically enters through cracked or fissured nipples during breastfeeding. It can produce toxins and form abscesses if left untreated.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile \u003Cstrong\u003EStreptococcus pyogenes\u003C/strong\u003E can cause mastitis, it is less common. \u003Cstrong\u003EHaemophilus influenzae\u003C/strong\u003E rarely causes breast infections, being more commonly associated with respiratory tract infections. \u003Cstrong\u003EPseudomonas aeruginosa\u003C/strong\u003E is an opportunistic pathogen that rarely causes primary mastitis. \u003Cstrong\u003EClostridium perfringens\u003C/strong\u003E is an anaerobic organism that would be an extremely rare cause of mastitis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETreatment typically involves continued breastfeeding or breast milk expression, adequate analgesia, and appropriate antibiotics targeting \u003Cem\u003EStaphylococcus aureus\u003C/em\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Staphylococcus aureus is the most common causative organism in mastitis, typically entering through nipple fissures during breastfeeding.","Mastitis presents as a painful, erythematous, and swollen breast, often accompanied by systemic symptoms like fever."],"references":["C\u00f4t\u00e9-Gravel J, Malouin F. Symposium review: Features of Staphylococcus aureus mastitis pathogenesis that guide vaccine development strategies. J Dairy Sci. 2019 May;102(5):4727-4740. doi: 10.3168/jds.2018-15272. Epub 2018 Dec 20. PMID: 30580940.","Blackmon MM, Nguyen H, Mukherji P. Acute Mastitis. [Updated 2023 Jul 21]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK557782/","Pevzner M, Dahan A. Mastitis While Breastfeeding: Prevention, the Importance of Proper Treatment, and Potential Complications. J Clin Med. 2020 Jul 22;9(8):2328. doi: 10.3390/jcm9082328. PMID: 32707832; PMCID: PMC7465810.","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press.","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52198"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16200"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52198","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52198"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-01T20:49:36+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-01T20:50:14+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8891"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66744"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/a